Parliament, Monday, 18 May 2020 –The Standing Committee on Finance, together with the Select Committee on Finance will tomorrow hold a virtual joint meeting to consider and adopt the committee report on the strategic and Annual Performance Plans (APP’s) of the National Treasury and the South African Revenue Services (Sars).
	
	The National Treasury and Sars appeared before the two committees on 5 May 2020 to present their strategic plans and APPs for the 2020/21 financial year, as well as the Medium Term Strategic Framework (MTSF) for 2020-2025. The National Treasury presented an estimated annual budget of R33.1 billion for the current financial year.
	
	Later on, The Portfolio Committee on Mineral Resources and Energy will hold two separate virtual meetings at noon and in the evening to be briefed by the National Radio-active Waste Disposal Institute, the National Nuclear Regulator, the Mine Health and Safety Council, the South African Energy Development Institute and the South African Energy Corporation on their respective APPs and budgets.
	
	Details of the meetings are as follows:
	Standing and Select Committees on Finance
	Date:  Tuesday, 19 May 2020
	Time:  09:00-12:00
	
	Portfolio Committee on Mineral Resources and Energy
	Date:  Tuesday, 19 May 2020
	Time:  12:00-15:00, as well as 18:00-21:00
	
	Members of the media who would like to be part of the meeting to observe may forward their contact details to Mr Mlindi Mpindi on 081 716 7329 for inclusion in the Parliament Communications Service WhatsApp group, where login details will be shared.
	
